          "id": 8,
          "question": "<p><a name=\"8281\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>Suppose \\( L = \\left\\{ p, q, r, s, t\\right\\} \\) is a lattice represented by the following Hasse diagram:</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"images/gateOverflow_pyq_images/discrete_mathematics___set_theory_and_algebra___lattice/3a4d856a629d88a89a83efe233aeabc1.png\"></p>\n\n<p>For any \\( x, y \\in L \\), not necessarily distinct , \\( x \\vee y \\) and \\( x \\wedge y \\) are join and meet of \\( x, y \\), respectively. Let \\( L^3&nbsp;= \\left\\{\\left(x, y, z\\right): x, y, z \\in L\\right\\} \\) be the set of all ordered triplets of the elements of \\( L \\). Let \\( p_{r} \\) be the probability that an element \\( \\left(x, y,z\\right) \\in L^3 \\)&nbsp;chosen equiprobably satisfies \\( x \\vee (y \\wedge z) = (x \\vee &nbsp;y) \\wedge (x \\vee &nbsp;z) \\). Then</p>\n\n</div><br><br><b>GATE CSE 2015 Set 1 | Question: 34</b></p>",
